<subSubSection id="502CC8EB389839F53B82B054C12A445E" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="785B5EA78496119F975029497B0BE2EB" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1D2388602E508F354923F1C0BC8ED855" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Colonial brachycnemic zoantharians with sand/detritus incrustation in the ectoderm and mesoglea. Currently, all species except for two described are zooxanthellate (
<bibRefCitation id="33F806E4B25A1EA6AFA7B0B0980B957C" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.478.8512" author="Irei, Y" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" refId="B157" refString="Irei, Y, Sinniger, F, Reimer, JD, 2015. Descriptions of two azooxanthellate Palythoa (Order Zoantharia: Subclass Hexacorallia) species from the Ryukyu Archipelago, southern Japan. ZooKeys 478: 1-26. https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.478.8512" title="Descriptions of two azooxanthellate Palythoa (Order Zoantharia: Subclass Hexacorallia) species from the Ryukyu Archipelago, southern Japan. ZooKeys 478: 1 - 26." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.478.8512" year="2015">Irei et al. 2015</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FA848AF0EB119F8E492BAE28680F897F" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="FBAC16F653DA4343984CF341CA7CA4AC" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3EAD44B3DA41EEDA910F09FE4FE3A93E" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Specimens examined with a sphincter muscle of linear mesogleal type (
<bibRefCitation id="33246BA0F64F4E371E91E0B9AA97EEB4" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1186/s12862-015-0406-1" author="Swain, TD" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" refId="B284" refString="Swain, TD, Schellinger, JL, Strimaitis, AM, Reuter, KE, 2015. Evolution of anthozoan polyp retraction mechanisms: convergent functional morphology and evolutionary allometry of the marginal musculature in order Zoanthidea (Cnidaria: Anthozoa: Hexacorallia). BMC Evolutionary Biology 15(123): 1-19. https://doi.org/10.1186/s12862-015-0406-1" title="Evolution of anthozoan polyp retraction mechanisms: convergent functional morphology and evolutionary allometry of the marginal musculature in order Zoanthidea (Cnidaria: Anthozoa: Hexacorallia). BMC Evolutionary Biology 15 (123): 1 - 19." url="https://doi.org/10.1186/s12862-015-0406-1" year="2015">Swain et al. 2015</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="99507C86E9988E82818C602172FD59B1" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<taxonomicName id="7D36FADE7927B59C20ECB0FE75435AAE" authority="Verrill, 1900" authorityName="Verrill" authorityYear="1900" class="Anthozoa" family="Zoanthidae" genus="Protopalythoa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Protopalythoa" order="Zoantharia" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="99E4E5BCB2B167A6404C75CFE913CFA4" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Protopalythoa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was originally separated from 
<taxonomicName id="5CC31A81084348306E8DEDFE7103AC93" authorityName="Lamouroux" authorityYear="1816" class="Hydrozoa" family="Sphenopidae" genus="Palythoa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Palythoa" order="Zoantharia" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="BD81BFC1947DD5591D1C5820092A444C" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Palythoa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on primarily polyp shape. Pax (1910) recommended merging 
<taxonomicName id="21D4117C1525EEE8146575A73DBE7168" authorityName="Lamouroux" authorityYear="1816" class="Hydrozoa" family="Sphenopidae" genus="Palythoa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Palythoa" order="Zoantharia" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="299FDEC52980617BAB0FD8C842C9D67D" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Palythoa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="8E01DC4F81E85D38870AC1A346FDDA57" authority="Verrill, 1900" authorityName="Verrill" authorityYear="1900" class="Anthozoa" family="Zoanthidae" genus="Protopalythoa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Protopalythoa" order="Zoantharia" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="1A93E3030173F621A4ABCB499DEDEF60" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Protopalythoa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and he defined three groups; 
<normalizedToken id="F29701385542185E7BEC975AE3BED664" originalValue="“immersae”">&quot;immersae&quot;</normalizedToken>
, 
<normalizedToken id="EEAAA1FE257CB63CC0217DAD5E184F80" originalValue="“intermediae”">&quot;intermediae&quot;</normalizedToken>
and 
<normalizedToken id="672AF609EDB576E46F044E5EB4C30DC3" originalValue="“liberae”">&quot;liberae&quot;</normalizedToken>
, which have no taxonomic rank (see 
<bibRefCitation id="6F843B9E791EDBFC5A296491C43053B9" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1071/IS02008" author="Ryland, JS" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" refId="B247" refString="Ryland, JS, Lancaster, JE, 2003. Revision of methods for separating species of Protopalythoa (Hexacorallia: Zoanthidea) in the tropical West Pacific. Invertebrate Systematics 17(3): 407-428. https://doi.org/10.1071/IS02008" title="Revision of methods for separating species of Protopalythoa (Hexacorallia: Zoanthidea) in the tropical West Pacific. Invertebrate Systematics 17 (3): 407 - 428." url="https://doi.org/10.1071/IS02008" year="2003">Ryland and Lancaster 2003</bibRefCitation>
). In 1923, Carlgren adopted this inclusive nomenclature. Similarly, 
<bibRefCitation id="E406FAF2127D500D72C9F47708DC194D" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1007/s003380050060" author="Burnett, WJ" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" refId="B39" refString="Burnett, WJ, Benzie, JAH, Beardmore, JA, Ryland, JS, 1997. Zoanthids (Anthozoa, Hexacorallia) from the Great Barrier Reef and Torres Strait, Australia: systematics, evolution and a key to species. Coral Reefs 16(1): 55-68. https://doi.org/10.1007/s003380050060" title="Zoanthids (Anthozoa, Hexacorallia) from the Great Barrier Reef and Torres Strait, Australia: systematics, evolution and a key to species. Coral Reefs 16 (1): 55 - 68." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/s003380050060" year="1997">Burnett et al. (1997)</bibRefCitation>
discussed the need to merge these genera but retained 
<taxonomicName id="D09D5FED3A3F49BC9104516D66A5E38B" authority="Verrill, 1900" authorityName="Verrill" authorityYear="1900" class="Anthozoa" family="Zoanthidae" genus="Protopalythoa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Protopalythoa" order="Zoantharia" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E0B9820AFD8E31A33F6E92E7D7EF46FB" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Protopalythoa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="449BE5B7EF4BF69BCC71627DF2E4758A" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1071/IS02008" author="Ryland, JS" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" refId="B247" refString="Ryland, JS, Lancaster, JE, 2003. Revision of methods for separating species of Protopalythoa (Hexacorallia: Zoanthidea) in the tropical West Pacific. Invertebrate Systematics 17(3): 407-428. https://doi.org/10.1071/IS02008" title="Revision of methods for separating species of Protopalythoa (Hexacorallia: Zoanthidea) in the tropical West Pacific. Invertebrate Systematics 17 (3): 407 - 428." url="https://doi.org/10.1071/IS02008" year="2003">Ryland and Lancaster (2003)</bibRefCitation>
also discussed this issue and argued to keep 
<taxonomicName id="33A4130C55AEE1A877DFDD4BAEDC047B" authority="Verrill, 1900" authorityName="Verrill" authorityYear="1900" class="Anthozoa" family="Zoanthidae" genus="Protopalythoa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Protopalythoa" order="Zoantharia" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CDEB00A8C0B0E4AD49E5CBD0BD4BB775" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Protopalythoa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
citing additional characters (zooxanthellate eggs in 
<taxonomicName id="601C0B6D0C2042DF1673E06086A264F1" authority="Verrill, 1900" authorityName="Verrill" authorityYear="1900" class="Anthozoa" family="Zoanthidae" genus="Protopalythoa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Protopalythoa" order="Zoantharia" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="345BF94E0FAFB3A65AB5D02A625150BD" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Protopalythoa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; afterwards potentially observed in 
<taxonomicName id="87823FC1A8575FF05E26870710B5672E" authorityName="Lamouroux" authorityYear="1816" class="Hydrozoa" family="Sphenopidae" genus="Palythoa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Palythoa" order="Zoantharia" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3272917F184F3E9FAAD28F6745991E42" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Palythoa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp. (Shiroma et al. 2010)). Herein, based on the several recent molecular studies (
<bibRefCitation id="1AAD5D38407C86A817BBAD6207355DE3" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1007/s00227-005-0016-3" author="Sinniger, F" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" refId="B269" refString="Sinniger, F, Montoya-Burgos, JI, Chevaldonne, P, Pawlowski, J, 2005. Phylogeny of the order Zoantharia (Anthozoa, Hexacorallia) based on the mitochondrial ribosomal genes. Marine Biology 147(5): 1121-1128. https://doi.org/10.1007/s00227-005-0016-3" title="Phylogeny of the order Zoantharia (Anthozoa, Hexacorallia) based on the mitochondrial ribosomal genes. Marine Biology 147 (5): 1121 - 1128." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/s00227-005-0016-3" year="2005">Sinniger et al. 2005</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="E90483FBAAE9FF252A5BBF59C072FC88" DOI="https://doi.org/10.2108/zsj.23.261" author="Reimer, JD" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" refId="B224" refString="Reimer, JD, Ono, S, Iwama, A, Takishita, K, Tsukahara, J, Maruyama, T, 2006. Morphological and molecular revision of Zoanthus (Anthozoa: Hexacorallia) from southwestern Japan, with descriptions of two new species. Zoological Science 23(3): 261-275. https://doi.org/10.2108/zsj.23.261" title="Morphological and molecular revision of Zoanthus (Anthozoa: Hexacorallia) from southwestern Japan, with descriptions of two new species. Zoological Science 23 (3): 261 - 275." url="https://doi.org/10.2108/zsj.23.261" year="2006">Reimer et al. 2006</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="D46DCB396F10BF39C1EAAA05F14B2882" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1007/s00338-007-0210-5" author="Reimer, JD" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" refId="B226" refString="Reimer, JD, Takishita, K, Ono, S, Maruyama, T, 2007b. Diversity and evolution in the zoanthid genus Palythoa (Cnidaria: Hexacorallia) utilizing nuclear ITS-rDNA. Coral Reefs 26(2): 399-410. https://doi.org/10.1007/s00338-007-0210-5" title="Diversity and evolution in the zoanthid genus Palythoa (Cnidaria: Hexacorallia) utilizing nuclear ITS-rDNA. Coral Reefs 26 (2): 399 - 410." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/s00338-007-0210-5" year="2007 b">2007b</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="9DACC21300182AF898A2C6D7B1D65F0F" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1155/2012/856079" author="Reimer, JD" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" refId="B234" refString="Reimer, JD, Foord, C, Irei, Y, 2012a. Species diversity of shallow water zoanthids (Cnidaria: Anthozoa: Hexacorallia) in Florida. Journal of Marine Biology 2012: article 856079 [14 pp.]. https://doi.org/10.1155/2012/856079" title="Species diversity of shallow water zoanthids (Cnidaria: Anthozoa: Hexacorallia) in Florida. Journal of Marine Biology 2012: article 856079 [14 pp.]." url="https://doi.org/10.1155/2012/856079" year="2012 a">2012a</bibRefCitation>
), we formally synonymise 
<taxonomicName id="47A5358B09ABF84691EBA3F6231FF6E9" authorityName="Lamouroux" authorityYear="1816" class="Hydrozoa" family="Sphenopidae" genus="Palythoa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Palythoa" order="Zoantharia" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2B2836D91CC61D83F60AE76993A6C5D3" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Palythoa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="612E3DC4B8668842438614CECEBD4A9F" authority="Verrill, 1900" authorityName="Verrill" authorityYear="1900" class="Anthozoa" family="Zoanthidae" genus="Protopalythoa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Protopalythoa" order="Zoantharia" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="35CB92F233B48B1C0BFBB9D86C04E96C" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Protopalythoa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with 
<taxonomicName id="B3CC178755CAEC92B67F6D8987173D34" authorityName="Lamouroux" authorityYear="1816" class="Hydrozoa" family="Sphenopidae" genus="Palythoa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Palythoa" order="Zoantharia" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8A6635A3FC147862354D8A29CB99C48F" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Palythoa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
having priority.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E027279794F1CAC0A03F69577C95963F" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Although at least 272 species-group names have been established in the genera 
<taxonomicName id="30145A49A0AA5629D2CF7780309B91D1" authorityName="Lamouroux" authorityYear="1816" class="Hydrozoa" family="Sphenopidae" genus="Palythoa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Palythoa" order="Zoantharia" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4E638BCB97E6D3A749BA02306387E6EA" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Palythoa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="34E6D878145CAFEA053BBC6CE5DB0DDD" authority="Verrill, 1900" authorityName="Verrill" authorityYear="1900" class="Anthozoa" family="Zoanthidae" genus="Protopalythoa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Protopalythoa" order="Zoantharia" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="366102D14FB5CE0E841675BE11A0A549" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Protopalythoa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the literature (see 
<bibRefCitation id="41EEC807FB7DBE152266360D3EE1C0E6" author="Fautin, DG" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" publicationUrl="http://www.kgs.ku.edu/Hexacoral/" refId="B95" refString="Fautin, DG, Buddemeier, RW, 2008. Biogeoinformatics of the Hexacorals. http://www.kgs.ku.edu/Hexacoral/" title="Biogeoinformatics of the Hexacorals." url="http://www.kgs.ku.edu/Hexacoral/" year="2008">Fautin and Buddemeier 2008</bibRefCitation>
), with more research, these species-group names will likely be found to be synonyms-the result of high level of intraspecific morphological variation (see 
<bibRefCitation id="79BFF131F025B093B8BD81EC1444EE8C" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1007/BF00349484" author="Burnett, WJ" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" refId="B37" refString="Burnett, WJ, Benzie, JAH, Beardmore, JA, Ryland, JS, 1994. High genetic variability and patchiness in a common Great Barrier Reef zoanthid (Palythoa caesia). Marine Biology 121(1): 153-160. https://doi.org/10.1007/BF00349484" title="High genetic variability and patchiness in a common Great Barrier Reef zoanthid (Palythoa caesia). Marine Biology 121 (1): 153 - 160." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/BF00349484" year="1994">Burnett et al. 1994</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="5B2BC9F5A7BDAC6E38E471CA70DB70C1" DOI="https://doi.org/10.2108/zsj.23.261" author="Reimer, JD" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" refId="B224" refString="Reimer, JD, Ono, S, Iwama, A, Takishita, K, Tsukahara, J, Maruyama, T, 2006. Morphological and molecular revision of Zoanthus (Anthozoa: Hexacorallia) from southwestern Japan, with descriptions of two new species. Zoological Science 23(3): 261-275. https://doi.org/10.2108/zsj.23.261" title="Morphological and molecular revision of Zoanthus (Anthozoa: Hexacorallia) from southwestern Japan, with descriptions of two new species. Zoological Science 23 (3): 261 - 275." url="https://doi.org/10.2108/zsj.23.261" year="2006">Reimer et al. 2006</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="6314F90030A53DDEC8059DC3D2408A1A" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1007/s10750-013-1587-5" author="Hibino, Y" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" refId="B140" refString="Hibino, Y, Todd, PA, Yang, S-Y, Benayahu, Y, Reimer, JD, 2014. Molecular and morphological evidence for conspecificity of two common Indo-Pacific species of Palythoa (Cnidaria: Anthozoa). Hydrobiologia 733 (1): 31-43. https://doi.org/10.1007/s10750-013-1587-5" title="Molecular and morphological evidence for conspecificity of two common Indo-Pacific species of Palythoa (Cnidaria: Anthozoa). Hydrobiologia 733 (1): 31 - 43." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/s10750-013-1587-5" year="2014">Hibino et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
